The paper deals with developing methods for detecting outliers in continuous-time event sequences. This involves statistical modeling and hypothesis testing, which are common techniques used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of point processes, which are commonly used in statistical modeling of event sequences (cs.ST). The application of the proposed methods is demonstrated on real-world clinical data, which falls under the category of computational biology (cs.CR). Finally, the paper does not deal with any specific hardware or system architecture, ruling out categories such as cs.AR and cs.OS.
